---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navigation from "../../components/Navigation.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="DailyDine Case Study">
  <Navigation />

  <main id="main-content" class="flex-1 max-w-[68ch] mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-24 flex flex-col gap-12 font-sans">
    
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <div class="flex gap-2 text-xs text-[#71717A] font-mono">
        <span>Work</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>Case Study</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-display font-medium text-[#FAFAFA] tracking-tight leading-tight">
        DailyDine
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] italic">
        "Build things that still make sense a decade later."
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Case Study Content -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-12 text-[#FAFAFA] text-base leading-[1.7] tracking-tight font-normal">
      
      <!-- Why We Built It -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">Why We Built DailyDine</h2>
        <p>
          Restaurant reservations are often managed by expensive, closed-source platforms.
          Venues pay high commissions for simple scheduling functionality.
          We built DailyDine to provide local restaurants with independent reservation software.
          The goal was to make dining coordination simple and cost-effective.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- The Biggest Mistake -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">The Biggest Mistake</h2>
        <p>
          We initially built a complex real-time seat tracking engine.
          This system used WebSockets to stream table layouts to all browsers.
          It quickly created desynchronization bugs under high concurrent write loads.
          This taught us that complex state streaming is rarely worth the operational cost.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- The Architecture -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">The Architecture</h2>
        <p>
          DailyDine runs on a Go API backend paired with a PostgreSQL database.
          The user interface is a static React client built with Tailwind CSS.
          API communication uses simple JSON payloads for predictable parsing.
          The system operates securely inside isolated server containers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Trade-offs -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">Trade-offs</h2>
        <p>
          We replaced WebSockets with database transaction locks and client-side polling.
          This increases network requests slightly but makes reservation flows predictable.
          Simple polling is robust and requires no persistent connection monitoring.
          We traded real-time animations for system reliability and simplicity.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Lessons -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">Lessons</h2>
        <p>
          Simple database transactions are easier to maintain than distributed state machines.
          Over-engineering early in product design adds unnecessary maintenance overhead.
          Clear database design is often the most reliable solution.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Links / GitHub -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3 border-t border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.08)] pt-6">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">Source Code</h2>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-xs font-mono">
          <a href="https://github.com/programmer-nick234/dailydine" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[#2563EB] hover:underline">
            GitHub Repository
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>

    <!-- Tech Stack footer -->
    <footer class="flex flex-col gap-6 border-t border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.08)] pt-8 mt-4 text-xs font-mono text-[#71717A]">
      <span>Technologies: Go · React · PostgreSQL · Tailwind CSS</span>
    </footer>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
